items.text:
Casting Call for Short 10-15 minutes called Repossession 

This is a  darkly comic short about ambition, fame, and the unexpected horrors lurking behind a routine job.

Casting call for the characters 
Kyle
 A seasoned presenter clinging to relevance in a changing media landscape. Desperate for a comeback, he takes one last job‚Äîblinded by ambition, even when the warning signs turn supernatural.
 Playing Age: Early 30s to mid 40s
 Ethnicity: Any
 Gender: Male
Spencer
 Kyle‚Äôs loyal second-in-command, tasked with shaping the show‚Äôs content. Often dragged into eerie locations, Spencer must confront whether he‚Äôs valued as a partner‚Äîor just a pawn.
 Playing Age: Mid 20s to Mid 30s
 Ethnicity: Any
 Gender: Male
Carla Curses
 A flashy social media psychic with a massive following and a hunger for viral fame. Her pursuit of a haunted object leads to possession‚Äîtransforming her into something savage and inhuman.
 Playing Age: 20s to 30s
 Ethnicity: Any
 Gender: Female
Frank
Carla‚Äôs trusted cameraman, now shattered by the night‚Äôs horrors. Haunted and fragile, his trauma slowly pulls him into the house‚Äôs darkness.
Playing Age: 30s to 40s
Ethnicity: Any
Physicality: Tall and lanky
Gender: Male

Filming will take place in the Liverpool/Merseyside area, United Kingdom. Looking to film middle to end of January 2026 
Please apply only if you're based locally.
For more details, contact: houndsoftheroundtable@gmail.com

Please note we do not reply to comments or direct Facebook messages. Thank you!

It‚Äôs a wrap! Six Commercials with 50 Actors from MA to TX to RI and back to RI for 3 more this week!!  4 Picture cars in TX - RI!! Locations in RI!  

On Set Wrangler, Child Welfare Worker and Production Assistant!  

Catering and Crafty for 4 days! 

I have a new business: ACTORDASH - I don‚Äôt just cast ‚Äòem! I deliver them to set!

I jumped in feet first starting in August 2025, and although we still have some administrative work to do; we are officially wrapped!

I am now on Holiday Break and will be gearing up for more filming in January 2026!

During this break I will be doing a massive Talent Scout starting in Rhode Island!

I know I can easily find everyone I need for our Massachusetts needs with a simple post! But, I‚Äôve found it harder to find Actors in Rhode Island.

I am also planning a Karaoke Holiday Party for the first time since before Covid!  If you‚Äôd like to attend send an email to:

JodiPurdyCasting@gmail.com
Subj:  Holiday Party 2025

On another good note - my client is looking into signing a SAG Contract in 2026!  

But for the time being I will be casting Non-Union Actors and Real People to portray Doctors, Nurses, Medical Personnel and Patients from all walks of life living in Rhode Island.

Submit to:

JodiPurdyCasting@gmail.com
Subj: RI Resident NU Actor Real Person

Share:

Jodi Purdy (Name)
111-111-1111 (cell)
jodipurdycasting@gmail.com (email)
Weymouth, MA (location)

DO NOT TYPE (name, cell, email, location) ONLY YOUR INFO which I cut and paste!

Share:

Photos, videos, reels, links, resume, etc.

Celebrating tonight at the Orpheum Theater in Boston at a Dark Star Orchestra show with 3 of my besties!!

Seeking Body Double for banking project shoot - Richmond VA - 11/24 & 11/25 - SAG

NEW PROJECT JUST IN!  Here is what we know/need:

Seeking Body Double for upcoming SAG project as follows:

Location:  Richmond VA

Dates 11/24 & 11/25

SAG Shoot

Rate:  SAG buy out rate is $469.90 / 8 hours

Talent needed:

Seeking body double for Antoine Craig, who is an African American blind soccer player.  He is 6‚Äô tall and 43 years old.  Ideally this person has some running and soccer abilities.

If you are available and interested in being considered, please email headshot, current snapshot, current full body shot, resume (if you have one) along with:

Full name

Current height 

Current weight

Union status

Comfortability with running

## **CASTING CALL ‚Äì ‚ÄúTale of Two‚Äù (Short Film)**

**Logline:**
*‚ÄúTale of Two‚Äù* is a portrait short film about women‚Äôs strength, focusing on our shared experiences rather than our differences. Through small, intimate scenes, we witness key moments in the lives of two women as they navigate hardship, love, and resilience in parallel journeys.

**Production Details:**
* **Location:** Downtown Vancouver
* **Shoot Dates:** 1-3 days ‚Äì end of January
* **Format:** MOS (no sync sound) ‚Äì performances will rely heavily on expressive, facial acting
* **Union Status:** Non-Union / Volunteer Passion Project
* **Compensation:** Volunteer basis with **great meals, greater company, and IMDb credit**.
Select roles (requiring multiple full days) will receive a **small honorarium**.

**To Submit:**
Please send your **headshot and CV/demo reel**, which **role** you‚Äôre applying for and a **self-tape** with the attached actions **taleoftwofilm@gmail.com**.
Include a **slate** with your **name, age, height,** and any **unavailable dates**.
**Submission Deadline:** *November 25th at midnight.*

Casting Call!

*Starchild* is a sci-fi drama that follows the story of two scientists, Vanessa and Tanner as they take separate paths to deal with their grief. Vanessa through faith, and Tanner through science. It's not until they discover the origins of life itself, that they reconcile to start a family of their own. 

The film is heartfelt, honest, and powerful.

Please send resume, headshot, and (if applicable) demo reel to starchildcasting@gmail.com

I am a 2nd year film production student at UCA in Farnham, Surrey.

We are currently in the process of trying to find extras for our film that we are shooting in sugar shack (the old pop world) in Portsmouth. Due to the brief we can only have people who are 18+ the dates we will be needing you are the 17th and 19th of November 9am-5pm, dress code will be club attire. As we are only students and have a very limited budget we won‚Äôt be able to pay you for this role but we will provide catering, as well as this you will be mentioned in the credits of the film and this will be submitted to film festivals. If you have any questions or are interested please email me via - maddiewest2006@icloud.com or private message me alternatively you can find me on instagram filmsbymads06.

Thank you.

topComments.text: So happy to pay for festivals but not cast or crew?
Avoid, they have no interest in paying for people's time, only fame.

üìç Brighton | üé• Filming Feb - Mar 2026 | üí∑ Paid (Equity rates)

Hey everyone! We‚Äôre casting for our graduation short film BITE, shooting in Brighton early next year.

BITE follows Billy‚Äôs attempt to navigate his father‚Äôs increasing alcoholism, volatility, and ostracisation. Set in 00s Britain, the film aims to address themes of family dysfunction, class, and the cyclical nature of trauma.

‚Ä¢ Dog presence on set

‚Ä¢ Final-year student film

‚Ä¢ Must be local to Brighton or willing to travel

ROLES:

BILLY MULLEN (14‚Äì18) ‚Äì A troubled, sharp-minded teenager trying to hold things together at home. Reserved, intuitive, sees more than he should.

KEV MULLEN (35‚Äì45) ‚Äì A once proud working-class man, who lost his job and most of his pride with it. He‚Äôs volatile, quietly intense, unpredictable, but beneath the exterior is a man scared of his own failure; desperate not to be forgotten, or worse, pitied.

3 OLDER BOYS (18+) ‚Äì No lines

Local boys who give Billy a hard time.

2 NOSY WOMEN (30s‚Äì40s) ‚Äì No lines

Neighbourhood gossip, all looks and whispers.

LOCAL BUTCHER (40s‚Äì50s) ‚Äì No lines

Grumpy, weathered, says it all without words.

To apply: Send your headshot, CV (or Spotlight link), and availability to 1195873@sfsstudents.ac.uk with the subject line: BITE ‚Äì [Role]

sharedPost.text:
I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies and some kind of Art House Underground Movies. I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.

I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch

Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928

Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 

please ask for details.

CASTING CALL - MUSIC VIDEO

Hello! I am a casting director in London looking for a man in his 40s to play a Dealer in a music video shooting on 24th November. 

We are specifically looking for someone who can do card tricks to be the card dealer. A Doug Jones looking character but not necessarily. Could this be you? 

The shoot is set in a poker bar and the plot of the music video is a heist. The pay rate for the Dealer is ¬£200 for the day. 

If you are interested - please email me ASAP with -recent headshot -full name -instagram handle -phone number -email

‚Äî‚Äî > lily.lepage@free.fr

items.text:
# **CASTING CALL FOR:**
# **ACTORS, VOICE ACTORS, SINGERS/VOCALISTS**
## 
# *' he lives here. '*

MANCHESTER BASED ONLY 

From writer/director/producer Jacob James Ward 

Watch my showreel here:

[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gIponbMURSU](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gIponbMURSU)

'he lives here.'

A sleepless corporate worker is forced to confront the monstrous embodiment of their childhood trauma during a terrifying sleep paralysis episode

A new gothic-noir, psychological thriller!

This project is deeply rooted in experimental film, with roles dominantly demanding body-performance with smaller amounts of spoken dialogue. 

This could be a good fit for those looking to get into experimental film with interests in deep character development/immersion within the horror/thriller genres! 

CASTING FOR 2 MAIN ROLES, VOICE ACTORS & VOCALISTS

BENNY

Male presenting, playing age 20-30

Benny, a reclusive loner caught between a draining job and worsening sleep paralysis partially due to unresolved trauma from his estranged father, battles his paranoia in an empty house

THE FIGURE 

Male presenting, playing age 20-30 

A manifestation of his deepest fears, the figure appears to Benny one evening in frightening hallucinations

VOICE ACTORS

Any age, but with a focus on more mature voices (40+) 

VOCALIST

To help in making the score of the film. Feminine-leaning vocals rooted in dreamy soundscapes and soft spoken word. Inspo: Phoebe Bridgers, Agnes Obel, Ethel Cain

Filming on dates in December (depending on actor availability) 

UNPAID STUDENT FILM 

MANCHESTER BASED ONLY 

Please reach out via this Facebook page or email at jacobward044@gmail.com 

to express interest and find out more info!

Much love 

X

# **CASTING CALL FOR:**
# **ACTORS, VOICE ACTORS, SINGERS/VOCALISTS**
## 
# *' he lives here. '*

MANCHESTER BASED ONLY 

From writer/director/producer Jacob James Ward 

Watch my showreel here:

[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gIponbMURSU](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gIponbMURSU)

'he lives here.'

A sleepless corporate worker is forced to confront the monstrous embodiment of their childhood trauma during a terrifying sleep paralysis episode

A new gothic-noir, psychological thriller!

This project is deeply rooted in experimental film, with roles dominantly demanding body-performance with smaller amounts of spoken dialogue. 

This could be a good fit for those looking to get into experimental film with interests in deep character development/immersion within the horror/thriller genres! 

CASTING FOR 2 MAIN ROLES, VOICE ACTORS & VOCALISTS

BENNY

Male presenting, playing age 20-30

Benny, a reclusive loner caught between a draining job and worsening sleep paralysis partially due to unresolved trauma from his estranged father, battles his paranoia in an empty house

THE FIGURE 

Male presenting, playing age 20-30 

A manifestation of his deepest fears, the figure appears to Benny one evening in frightening hallucinations

VOICE ACTORS

Any age, but with a focus on more mature voices (40+) 

VOCALIST

To help in making the score of the film. Feminine-leaning vocals rooted in dreamy soundscapes and soft spoken word. Inspo: Phoebe Bridgers, Agnes Obel, Ethel Cain

Filming on dates in December (depending on actor availability) 

UNPAID STUDENT FILM 

MANCHESTER BASED ONLY 

Please reach out via this Facebook page or email at jacobward044@gmail.com 

to express interest and find out more info!

Much love 

X

Join Lesley Joseph and Rob Rinder in conversation on Zoom on Sunday 23rd November at 11.00 amüé≠ 

Grab your coffee and settle in for a Sunday morning chat as Lesley Joseph lifts the curtain on her incredible five-decade career - from Birds of a Feather to the West End - in conversation with Rob Rinder.

Expect laughter, insight, and plenty of behind-the-scenes stories from life on stage and screen.

Plus, you‚Äôll have the chance to ask your own burning questions!

This special event is to help raise awareness and support for Actors‚Äô Trust and is free to attend.

Book your spot via the link: https://www.actorstrust.org.uk/.../qa-with-rob-rinder.../

Don‚Äôt miss it - see you there! üí¨

items.text:
Personal Short Film Project

SEEKING 2 ACTORS FOR MAIN CAST

WHEN: Dec 20‚Äì23, 2025

PAID: CAD $150 / Day

Project Title:

The Thought Experiment ‚ÄúMETA MONTAGE‚Äù

Genre:

Meta-psychological Drama / Experimental Metafiction / Postmodern Romance

Logline:

When a screenwriter finds himself inside the very film he‚Äôs writing, reality and fiction intertwine ‚Äî forcing him, his characters, and even the audience to confront the question: Who is truly creating whom?

A visual and interactive interpretation of the Multiverse Theory.

Production Details:

Dates: December 20‚Äì23, 2025

Location: Vancouver, BC

Rate: CAD $150 / day

Type: Independent Short Film (non-union, paid)

Casting:

JACK (30s)

An expressive man in his 30s. Starts as a victim tied to a chair but gradually becomes both the actor and writer of the film. Moves between fiction and reality, showing layers of vulnerability and control.

Keywords: Actor / Writer / Victim / Meta-role

Look: Half-dressed, sweaty, bloody ‚Üí later calm and casual.

NARRATOR (30s‚Äì40s)

A calm, mysterious man in a classic suit. Both inside and outside the film, he speaks directly to the camera as a philosophical observer. His emotions slowly break through his composed tone.

Keywords: Narrator / Observer / Director-like

Look: Formal, mustache, black & white lighting, under spotlight.

I‚Äôll be sending those who emailed me a 6-minute short film I recently shot, along with a script excerpt from the project.

I‚Äôd really appreciate it if you could send me a video of yourself reading the script by November 23

Contact:

Director / Writer / Producer : Yuri Kakuya

üìß hkjfilm@gmail.com

Hi everyone! I'm casting a **voice over commercial **for StatsCan, and we are looking for people (men and women, 25-75 years old) that can speak **Inuktitut. **These ads will run across TV, Web and Radio.

If you're interested in auditioning, please email me at: **adriennelindsaycasting@gmail.com** for details. I will send you the script of an ad we did a few years ago. To audition, you will need to record yourself reading the ad and send it in to me. We are looking for "official-sounding" reads.

**Specs**:

South Baffin (Inuktitut Nunavut) dialect.
*Talent can be based anywhere, but will need access to a professional recording studio to patch in.*

Usage: voice over commercial - multiple spots across TV, Web and Radio. Open to both ACTRA & non-union performers.

Thank you!

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚ÄîCASTING CALL FOR **THE GREEN PASSPORT**‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

We are students of Budapest Metropolitan University and currently in our 3rd year on Film and Media bachelors. For our Diploma Film we are looking for actors in 2 main roles. 

LOGLINE OF THE FILM:

In a midst of chaos caused by losing her passport on the first day of the visit, the mom and the son rediscover their long gone connection and love for each other. And the trip ends and they have to say goodbye when they finally reconnect with each other.

Below you can find the important infos about the characters:

CHARACTER‚ÄôS RACE
* South American
* South Asian

MARIA
* 50
* Nurse
* Overprotective, still distant
* Slightly closed minded
* Not expressive or vulnerable most of the time
* Caring but does not know how to 
* Kind
* Emotionally strong
* Ambitious
* From a working class family and saved up money to be in Europe
* Does not speak English well

ETHAN
* 20 - 27
* Lives in Europe
* Studies literature English
* Used to be sweet and naive but now more aware and mature
* Academically smart but not street smart 
* Gets overwhelmed easily 
* Anxious in stressful situations but manages to resolve them
* Expressive, shows emotions but not to the mum

ADDITIONAL INFO ABOUT THE PROJECT:
* This is a university film and our budget is very low, so this is an **UNPAID** work.
* The shooting most probably will happen in the 2nd part of April. 
* Before the shooting we will hold rehearsals (end March/ early April).
* The shooting will happen in the actors‚Äô native language, but the process of the shooting and the communication during the shoot will be English, so English language skills **REQUIRED**.

If you are interested please send us headshots and previous works of yourself to [thegreenpassport.work@gmail.com](mailto:thegreenpassport.work@gmail.com).

items.text:
**25th Anniversary Edition: International Physical Theatre Laboratory**

**December 13‚Äì22, 2025 | Schloss Laubegg, Austria**

*A transformative nine-day intensive bringing together theatre artists, dancers, choreographers, circus performers, and movement practitioners from around the world.*

The International Physical Theatre Laboratory has been a cornerstone of European physical theatre training since 2000, bringing together artists from around the world for intensive periods of artistic exchange, training, and creation. Organized by NIPAI (New International Performing Arts Institute), IPTL embodies the organization's mission to foster international collaboration and support the development of contemporary performance practices that transcend cultural and disciplinary boundaries.

Due to the intimate nature of the program and the desire to create a balanced, dynamic group, participation is limited to 15 artists. Selection is based on professional experience, artistic motivation, and the potential contribution each applicant can make to the collective laboratory experience.

**To learn more about the program, faculty, schedule, and practical details, visit: **

https://www.nipai.org/programs/international-physical-theatre-lab .

items.text:
Hey everyone,
I‚Äôm Michael Uchenik, a film student, and this December (11‚Äì16.12) I‚Äôll be shooting my graduation film in Berlin, a story that explores the connection between trauma, love, and the body.

The entire film takes place during a laid-back house chill party, a warm, vibrant space where something deeper quietly unfolds.
It tells the story of David, an Israeli man full of life on the outside but haunted by a trauma he can‚Äôt escape, and Leo, his German boyfriend who tries to love him hard enough to bring him back to the present.

It‚Äôs a film about the duality of what we show versus what we hide.
About love as an anchor, and how memories follow us even when we move far away.

I‚Äôm looking for open-minded people who feel comfortable in front of the camera and with their bodies to join as participants in the party scenes.
This is not a pornographic film, but a sensitive and artistic project that looks at intimacy and vulnerability in an honest way.

If this sounds interesting to you, here‚Äôs a link with more info.

https://forms.gle/ZZJw8THu6qSW6UoKA 

And please feel free to share it with anyone who might be a good fit üí´

Thank you so much,
Michael

Hi everyone! I‚Äôd love to invite you all to see our **award-nominated, five-star dark comedy** currently touring the UK that‚Äôs coming to London **next week** for a fortnight at the Drayton Arms in Kensington!

‚ÄòYes, he's in a celebrations tub. No, he's not in with the bounties.‚Äô

Aaron, an unemployed entertainer, has stolen his dad's ashes and hidden them in a tub of chocolates. As he journeys toward St. Ives to scatter them, we discover the reasons behind his theft, and witness a suspenseful chase with the police hot on his heels. 

Written and performed by Oscar Brudenall-Jones and directed by Esalan Gates (5-star, BroadwayWorld UK Nominee ‚Äì Best New Production), this dark comedy explores grief in a post-pandemic world, as well as sperm bank strikes and why you shouldn't lose your rag at an old person.

Produced by To The Tooth Theatre, this is comedy with a bite.

https://www.thedraytonarmstheatre.co.uk/maybe-i-should-stop

UPDATE: SUBMISSIONS ARE CLISING FOR NOW. THANK YOU EVERYONE WHO HAS SUBMITTED SO FAR. üôåüèΩ
______

üö® CASTING CALL ‚Äì FEATURE FILM üö® (RDE FILMS)

RDE Films is now accepting auditions for our upcoming feature film. We‚Äôre seeking bold, authentic performers with strong presence and emotional range. Following directions is extremely important to our process.

‚∏ª

AVAILABLE ROLES

Detective 1 ‚Äì Male, 25‚Äì35
Seasoned detective, weathered and street-smart with a strong personality.
Types: Jon Bernthal, Shia LaBeouf, Denzel Washington, Lakeith Stanfield, Benjamin Bratt.
Barrio-raised energy. (Willing to smoke fake herbal cigarettes.)

Detective 2 ‚Äì Male, 25‚Äì35
Experienced cop with a black-and-white view of justice.
Types: Lakeith Stanfield, Michael B. Jordan, Don Cheadle.
Raised in a good neighborhood; confident and disciplined.

Assistant District Attorney ‚Äì Male, 25‚Äì45
Strong personality, ‚Äúboss energy,‚Äù sharp and commanding. The quintessential lawyer type.

Killer ‚Äì Male, 30‚Äì45
Soft-spoken, intelligent, creepy, and quietly imposing.
Think Ed Gein, Arthur Fleck, Longlegs.

Racist Pastor ‚Äì Male, 35‚Äì55
Charismatic, silver-tongued, sly, and playful ‚Äî hides malice behind a smile.

items.text:
Hey everyone! My name is Jackson Smith and I'm a fourth year at CU Boulder working on my BFA thesis film! I'm looking to fill two lead rolls if anyone is interested:

Title: Intersection

Genre: Drama

Logline: The film follows three people who unexpectedly effect each other while trying to make their way through a normal day. Introspective and character-focused. Very open to collaboration!

Roles: 

**Kat (Female, ~18-24)**: A young adult trying to find her footing. Kat often finds herself pushing forward in an attempt to forget what is behind her. She has a troubled relationship with her mother and has not been in contact with her for some time. It is now the day of her mother's birthday and Kat feels obligated to get her a cake.

**Heather (Female, 30s/40s)**: Kat's mother, independent and headstrong. Currently working as a freelance consultant, she really had to hustle to get to where she is now. However, her success came at the cost of her personal relationships. Heather wishes she and her daughter could reconnect, but she's not sure how to go about it. It is now Heather's birthday.

Production Type: Student

Contact Information: jasm4113@colorado.edu, (720)525-9544

Run Time: Short, ~12 minutes

Compensation: Unpaid (there will be food)

Union Status: Non-Union

Shooting Schedule: Rehearsal on Friday the 21st, shooting on the 22nd and 23rd of November

Filming Location: Boulder, Pearl Street

CASTING CALL FOR NEW PLAY!
--------------------------------

A New Comedic play by Zack Faulks, *Bulimia is My Roman Empire* follows a group of Servants as they attempt to assassinate the Emperor. They discover that power may not be all that they had once desired. Learning that their target is engaged in a number of self-destructive behaviours, our conspirators are forced to follow down a long rabbit hole of strange diets, machismo, and fascism should they want to prove that they deserve the right to rule. As a satire of manhood, ultimately no one‚Äôs happy with where they end up.

For more information check out the images below!

Deadline to submit is Nov. 29, 2025 at 12:00pm.

--------------------
Find us at www.greattrashproductions.ca

items.text:
Casting Call (Non-Union) for COUPLES - Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of clients in a simulated therapy session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. The sessions include some scripted elements to prepare, and then some improv with prompts.

We are currently interested in filming with mature couples, queer couples, interracial couples, or throuples/polycules of various gender identity combinations. All ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are welcome. 

All experience levels with acting are welcome, including experienced actors with less experienced partners. We are committed to making this a respectful and safe process, with open communication and respect for boundaries.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are November 14 to 18, based on actor availability, but more will occur in the future so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is $90 CAD per performer, with the expectation of some prepared material, studio session duration: 1 hour

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume, as well as some information about you and your partner, such as gender identities, age, cultural/racial backgrounds. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again. We do sometimes receive more submissions than we are able to respond to, but we do read them all, and we do save your submissions for future consideration.

Still looking for volunteers for a Short film project who like to act in front of the camera.

The purpose of this short film is to create a new showreel for every actor and actress who‚Äôs gonna participate on it.

What's the movie supposed to be about?

A young man, once part of an underground operation supplying drugs to his boss, has since left the shady business to start a normal life.

Months later, he returns to the warehouse to surprise his former boss with a gift - but as he steps inside, he's struck by how much has changed. The familiar place now feels foreign, guarded, and tense.

After a brief, uneasy reunion, he runs into an old colleague, haunted by the past, does everything he can to avoid her before quickly leaving - closing the door on a life he's no longer part of.

Actors must be able to speak in English fluently!!

Open roles 

(Melly) Female, 18+

(Tasha) Female, 18+

(Maddie) Female, 18+

(Avi) Male, 45+

Extra 

Female & Male any ethnicity and 20+

For the spin

This will be shot in Cologne 

2 day between November 24-30 2025

If interested and available please send headshot to email officialemmanuelbenjamin@gmail.com

# **üéÑElf Work at Hertfordshire Zoo!üéÑ**

Hertfordshire Zoo is looking for jolly, enthusiastic, and festive individuals to bring the magic of Christmas to life this year at **Hertfordshire Zoo in Broxbourne, Hertfordshire.**

**What We‚Äôre Looking For:**
* A warm, friendly personality with plenty of festive spirit
* Confidence interacting with children and families
* Reliability and professionalism
* Previous performance or grotto experience (preferred but not essential)
* We have a mixture of performance elf and grotto elf work available

**When You‚Äôll Work:**

The dates we are currently still looking for people are:
* 26th November (4:30pm-8:30pm)
* 29th November (9:30am-4:00pm)
* 30th November (9:00am-5:00pm)
* 6th December (9:00am-5:00pm)
* 7th December (9:00am-5:00pm)
* 13th December (9:00am-5:00pm)
* 24th December (9:00am-3:00pm)

**PLEASE NOTE** - You are not required to be available to work on all of these dates. Any availability is accepted.

**What We Offer:**
* A fun and rewarding role in a magical setting
* ¬£14 per hour
* Full costume and training provided
* The chance to work at one of Hertfordshire's most loved attractions

If you would love to make Christmas unforgettable for our visitors, we‚Äôd love to hear from you.

Apply now by emailing **[entertainment@hertfordshirezoo.com](mailto:entertainment@hertfordshirezoo.com)**

items.text:
Hi! 

I‚Äôm currently casting a well paid shoot for an alcohol brand

As it‚Äôs advertising for alcohol all cast legally need to be at least 25 (production will ask for id to prove this if shortlisted by client) however the concept for the project is quite youthful so max age should be 30. 

Casting Brief: 

Looking for European girls with coloured hair (think red, blue, pink, green, berry, purple) or happy to have their hair coloured for the shoot. 

Looking for European boys with facial hair (a moustache and/or beard - bonus if you have an interesting hair cut too) 

This is a London shoot so looking for London based people only. 

**Shoot Dates: **Thursday 27th + Friday 28th November

Talent to attend both shoot days in London on Location

Based on a 10 hour shoot day including an additional hour for lunch

**Fitting Date:** Monday 24th November, 1-2 hours in London (between 9am and 6pm)

**Talent Age: **All Talent to be over 25 and passport or ID needs to be provided at the time of shortlist to confirm this 

**Talent Rates:**

Talent Day Rates - ¬£600 per person per day

Talent Usage* ¬£5,000 per model

*Usage not guaranteed however all talent are shot in groups so this is very likely to be confirmed

**Talent Wardrobe:**

Talent will be required to bring a couple of outfits to the shoot which will be briefed by the wardrobe stylist

and either brought to the fitting or photographed before the shoot.

¬£50 per person (total not per day)

To submit please fill in this form : 

[https://airtable.com/apprDbNv50EdHz0RT/pagpszb0AEzQg5XCi/form](https://airtable.com/apprDbNv50EdHz0RT/pagpszb0AEzQg5XCi/form)

And, please upload your self tape here: [https://www.dropbox.com/request/s2OXkOWhOSaif9oUoaCR](https://www.dropbox.com/request/s2OXkOWhOSaif9oUoaCR)

The deadline is 10AM, Monday 17th November. 

No requests, no PM‚Äôs 

Thank you! 

www.unit-c.co

CASTING CALL - MUSIC VIDEO

Hello! I am a casting director in London looking for a man in his 40s to play a Dealer in a music video shooting on 24th November. 

We are specifically looking for someone who can do card tricks to be the card dealer. A Doug Jones looking character but not necessarily. Could this be you? 

The shoot is set in a poker bar and the plot of the music video is a heist. The pay rate for the Dealer is ¬£200 for the day. 

If you are interested - please email me ASAP with -recent headshot -full name -instagram handle -phone number -email

‚Äî‚Äî > lily.lepage@free.fr

items.text:
Casting Call ‚Äì Lead Role ‚ÄúLil Messias‚Äù in Bachelor Film Groupies (The Norwegian Film School) - Paid! 

We are casting for Groupies, an ambitious and visually striking bachelor film by a talented team of students at The Norwegian Film School.

The film explores the groupie phenomenon through a music film about a rapper and a fangirl spending one surreal night backstage. Blending realism, stylization, and surreal imagery, Groupies delves into themes of power, status, gender roles, and what it truly means to be human in a superficial, image-driven world.

Role: Lil Messias (‚ÄúLil Mess‚Äù) ‚Äì Lead
Lil Messias is an internationally acclaimed rap artist.
On stage, he radiates confidence, sex appeal, and dominance ‚Äî the perfect image of modern masculinity.
Beneath the surface, however, he battles growing anxiety and emptiness in a life fueled by drugs, violence, and meaningless sex. He is trapped in his own image and longs to be truly seen. (Age 20-30)

This role involves:
 ‚Ä¢ An intimate scene with the character Ninni.
A professional intimacy coordinator will be attached to ensure a safe, respectful, and transparent process.
 ‚Ä¢ A rap performance, including recording a song and potentially some choreography.
 ‚Ä¢ The creative team will also be developing a full artist brand around the character ‚Äî an exciting opportunity to embody a complete on-screen persona.

Actors of all ethnicities and backgrounds are strongly encouraged to apply.

Production Details
 ‚Ä¢ Shooting period: Between January 20‚Äì30, 2025
 ‚Ä¢ Location: Norway
 ‚Ä¢ Compensation: According to Norwegian industry rates (Tariff)

Travel expenses will be covered. (Europe only)

If this sounds like something for you, please get in touch. Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

Please send location, portrait and if you have: showreel and/or introduction tape.

Email: deteramalie@gmail.com

items.text:
Exciting News !
I'm thrilled to share my book EDDIE'S BACK -- A gripping story that I believe would make a FANTASTIC MOVIE.

I've already WRITTEN AND COPYRIGHTED THE SCREENPLAY, so it's ready to go! Now, I'm reaching out to production companies, literary agents, film agents, and directors who might be interested in bringing this story to life on the big screen.

EDDIE'S BACK - May 1963, Eddie a popular teenager is intentionally hit by a car, which leaves him in a coma. It's 2025, Eddie wakes up. He is shocked and disappointed at what he sees. Until the ghost of JFK visits him and inspires him to make a difference.

Now Eddie 77 years young, realizes why he was kept alive and what he has to do.

However, a senior Senator with an agenda of his own is watching Eddie's every move and is prepared to stop his mission at any cost.

DREAM CAST (Just Imagining!)
#HarrisonFord - #CandyClark - #PaulLeMat - #RichardDreyfuss - #CharlesSDutton - #MarkWahlberg - #MatthewMcConaughey - #MargotRobbie - #RobertDeniro - #BradleyCooper - #TaylorSwift - #MorganFreeman - #NicolasCage - #GregKinnear - #AnneHathaway - #WillFerrell - #PatrickSchwarzenegger - #joancollins -#kellyopsal -#islacervelli - #JackHyde -#LaurenSanchez -#jeffbezos -#elonmusk -#JordonHudson -#parishilton 
DIRECTOR - #RonHoward

NO OFFICIAL TIES - JUST PUTTING IT OUT THERE AND HOPING TO GET EDDIE'S BACK INTO THE RIGHT HANDS!

TAGGING TOP AGENCIES:
#ImagineEntertainment - #IndependentArtistGroup - #WilliamMorrisEndeavor - #VerveTalentandLiteraryManagement - #TheWayneAgency - #CAA
And indie powerhouses like: #A24 - #AnnapurnaPictures - #PlanBEntertainment - #BlumhouseProductions - #KillerFilms - #Neon - #FilmNation - #BleeckerStreet - #ElaraPictures - #BigBeach

NO OFFICIAL TIES - Just putting it out there and hoping to get EDDIE'S BACK into THE RIGHT HANDS!

PRODUCTION COMPANIES I ADMIRE:
#SONYPICTURES - #WARNERBROSDISCOVERY - #IMAGEENTERTAINMENT - #WALTDISNEYPICTURES

PRODUCERS - I'd love to work with:
#MarkCiardi - #MattDamon - #MarkWahlberg - #WillFerrell - #TomHanks

NO OFFICIAL TIES - Just putting it out there and hoping to get EDDIE'S BACK into THE RIGHT HANDS!

#Eddie'sBack #BooktoFilm #Screenplayready #Filmadaptation #Moviepitch #Filmmakers #producers #directors #Independentfilm #IndieCinema #literaryAgents

WHAT IF EDDIE (HARPER) AND JOHN (MILLER) WERE FRIENDS IN 1963?

Let's make movie magic happen!

PEOPLE WILL COME!

They haven‚Äôt stepped foot in a movie theater in 40 years.
Not since the golden days of double features and balcony seats.
But one day, without even knowing why‚Ä¶
THEY GET IN THEIR CAR AND GO

Not for the stadium seating.
Not for the surround sound.
**But for something deeper. Something they‚Äôve been missing.**

They walk into the lobby ‚Äî wide-eyed, hearts open, like children.
The smell of popcorn. The hum of the projector.
A moment suspended in time.

They don‚Äôt blink when the clerk says, ‚ÄúTwenty dollars.
Because this isn‚Äôt a transaction ‚Äî it‚Äôs a Homecoming.

They find their old seats‚Ä¶ the very ones from their childhood.
And the screen lights up with a story that speaks to the soul.

**Eddie‚Äôs Back** isn‚Äôt just a movie.
It‚Äôs a bridge across generations.
A story that blends nostalgia, humor, and hope ‚Äî with just enough magic to make you believe again.

They will laugh.
They will cry.
And most importantly‚Ä¶
**They will remember.**

Baby Boomers will come.
They will bring their children.
Their grandchildren.
And one day ‚Äî their great-grandchildren.

Because *Eddie‚Äôs Back* reminds them of what was good‚Ä¶
**And what can still be good again.**

The one constant through all the years has been family films ‚Äî
**Stories that bring us together.**

Oh yes ‚Äî people will come.
Not because they need to‚Ä¶ but because their hearts tell them to!
And when they do‚Ä¶
**They‚Äôll thank you for bringing it to life.**

sharedPost.text:
Making Contact will be making a come back in 2026! 

Here‚Äôs a few pictures from the last course.

We asked: How do actors make contact? Sustainably, but with joy. With care, but with full-hearted engagement.

The workshop brought together the safety and agency of clear communication with the deep celebration of what it is to make contact with another human being. People leaned in and learned‚Äînot just how to uphold safe, positive, healthy boundaries, but also that it‚Äôs okay to lean in with pleasure, with joy. To delight in the presence and physical contribution of your scene partner.

#actortraining #londonactortraining #physicaltheatre #concentworkshop

Let‚Äôs be real for a moment‚Ä¶ üì∏

Headshots can sometimes feel like an extortionate expense - as a fellow actor, I get it. That‚Äôs why I keep my pricing fair, accessible, and realistic, without ever cutting corners on quality.

I see plenty of novice photographers grab a basic camera & kit lens then start offering ‚Äútoo good to be true‚Äù sessions in these groups for ¬£30‚Äì¬£100 promising they‚Äôll get you seen ‚Ä¶ but here‚Äôs the truth: Headshot photography is a specialist skill. Low end, inexpensive ‚Äúquick fix‚Äù sessions might seem attractive at first but buy cheap, buy twice. 

Invest in a real headshot session with an award-winning photographer who brings experience, artistry, and skill to the table and get it right the first time. I‚Äôm a working actor too so I‚Äôm in your shoes and evolve with the times to provide the most updated, admired form of headshots.

Expect powerful, cinematic portraits that casting directors always notice. Clients regularly tell me their new headshots have led to more auditions, more callbacks and booked work - that‚Äôs exactly what I aim for.

I‚Äôve had my fair share of awkward shoots; rushed sessions with cash grab cameramen who treated me like cattle, just another face passing through‚Ä¶ I started doing this job to change that.
When you book with me, it‚Äôs never rushed. We‚Äôll have a coffee, chat about your goals, play some tunes, and get you relaxed before the camera even comes out. My direction is creative and unorthodox - I‚Äôll get you talking, laughing, and thinking, so we capture real moments that show who YOU are, not just what you look like.

The results speak for themselves - my clients have gone on to appear in major TV shows, films, high-end commercials, and even land roles on the West End. Your headshot is often your first impression - let‚Äôs make sure it‚Äôs unforgettable.

üëâ View my portfolio: https://www.fandmmedia.co.uk/ryan-s-gallery

üëâ Book a showreel scene, cinematic monologue recording, self tape sessions & more: https://www.fandmmedia.co.uk

Ryan üì∏

items.text:
PART 7 ‚Äî ‚ÄúThe City Grew Quieter When She Spoke‚Äù

(First-person narration)

We spent more time together after that night‚Äîslowly, without forcing anything. Some days we walked without talking, letting the city speak for us. Other days we talked about everything: the dreams we chased, the people we lost, and the pieces of ourselves we were still trying to understand.

I began to notice the small things about her again‚Äîthings I thought I had forgotten:

How she paused before laughing, like she wanted to be sure it was safe.
How her eyes searched mine before she shared anything that mattered.
How she walked a little closer when the streets got louder, like my presence was a shield she didn‚Äôt want to admit she needed.

One evening, as the city lights blurred behind us, she said quietly:

> ‚ÄúYou know‚Ä¶ I didn‚Äôt come back just to see the city again. I came back because I wasn‚Äôt done learning what your presence does to my heart.‚Äù

I didn‚Äôt speak‚Äînot because I didn‚Äôt have words, but because hers were still traveling through me.

We sat on a bench near the bus station, watching headlights sweep across the pavement like fleeting miracles. She looked at me, holding her jacket close to her body.

> ‚ÄúWhen we were apart,‚Äù she continued, ‚ÄúI kept hearing the city the way you hear it. I saw shadows shaped like you. I don‚Äôt know what this is, but‚Ä¶ I don‚Äôt want to run from it anymore.‚Äù

I turned to her, my voice steady:

> ‚ÄúWe don‚Äôt have to name it yet. Let‚Äôs just walk it‚Ä¶ one sunrise at a time.‚Äù

Her shoulders relaxed. For the first time in a long time, she smiled without hiding it. There was peace‚Äîsoft, unfinished, but real.

And for a moment, the city wasn‚Äôt loud.
For a moment, it sounded like us.

Migo Palendrom  write up

items.text:
Hello! I am a casting director in London looking for a man in his 40s to play a Dealer in a music video shooting on 24th November. 

We are specifically looking for someone who can do card tricks to be the card dealer. A Doug Jones looking character but not necessarily. Could this be you? 

The shoot is set in a poker bar and the plot of the music video is a heist. The pay rate for the Dealer is ¬£200 for the day. 

If you are interested - please email me ASAP with -recent headshot -full name -instagram handle -phone number -email

‚Äî‚Äî > lily.lepage@free.fr

topComments.text: How about doug Jones with long hair, knuckle tattoos and grills?

items.text:
Hi! 

I‚Äôm currently casting a well paid shoot for an alcohol brand

As it‚Äôs advertising for alcohol all cast legally need to be at least 25 (production will ask for id to prove this if shortlisted by client) however the concept for the project is quite youthful so max age should be 30. 

Casting Brief: 

Looking for European girls with coloured hair (think red, blue, pink, green, berry, purple) or happy to have their hair coloured for the shoot. 

Looking for European boys with facial hair (a moustache and/or beard - bonus if you have an interesting hair cut too) 

This is a London shoot so looking for London based people only. 

**Shoot Dates: **Thursday 27th + Friday 28th November

Talent to attend both shoot days in London on Location

Based on a 10 hour shoot day including an additional hour for lunch

**Fitting Date:** Monday 24th November, 1-2 hours in London (between 9am and 6pm)

**Talent Age: **All Talent to be over 25 and passport or ID needs to be provided at the time of shortlist to confirm this 

**Talent Rates:**

Talent Day Rates - ¬£600 per person per day

Talent Usage* ¬£5,000 per model

*Usage not guaranteed however all talent are shot in groups so this is very likely to be confirmed

**Talent Wardrobe:**

Talent will be required to bring a couple of outfits to the shoot which will be briefed by the wardrobe stylist

and either brought to the fitting or photographed before the shoot.

¬£50 per person (total not per day)

To submit please fill in this form : 

[https://airtable.com/apprDbNv50EdHz0RT/pagpszb0AEzQg5XCi/form](https://airtable.com/apprDbNv50EdHz0RT/pagpszb0AEzQg5XCi/form)

And, please upload your self tape here: [https://www.dropbox.com/request/s2OXkOWhOSaif9oUoaCR](https://www.dropbox.com/request/s2OXkOWhOSaif9oUoaCR)

The deadline is 10AM, Monday 17th November. 

No requests, no PM‚Äôs 

Thank you! 

www.unit-c.co

We're looking for reliable, hardworking crew members to join our micro-budget independent feature film shooting in the Los Angeles area this December!

üìã POSITIONS AVAILABLE:

üîß SWING GRIP (1 Position)

‚Ä¢ Rate: California minimum wage

  - Wednesday, December 17, 2025

üé• PRODUCTION ASSISTANT #1

‚Ä¢ Rate: California minimum wage

‚Ä¢ Duties: Truck loading, driver transport

‚Ä¢ Dates & estimated hours:

  - Thursday, December 4 (3-4 hours)

  - Saturday, December 6 - Evening (2-3 hours)

  - Sunday, December 7 - Evening (2-3 hours)

  - Monday, December 8 - Evening (2-3 hours)

  - Tuesday, December 16 - Evening (2-3 hours)

  - Wednesday, December 17 - Evening (2-3 hours)

  - Thursday, December 18 (3-4 hours - truck unload)

üé• PRODUCTION ASSISTANT #2

‚Ä¢ Rate: California minimum wage

‚Ä¢ Duties: Truck loading, equipment handling

‚Ä¢ Dates & estimated hours:

  - Thursday, December 4 (3-4 hours)

  - Monday, December 8 - Evening (1-2 hours)

  - Tuesday, December 16 - Evening (1-2 hours)

  - Wednesday, December 17 - Evening (1-2 hours)

  - Thursday, December 18 (3-4 hours - truck unload)

üìç LOCATION: Los Angeles area

‚ú® WHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR:

‚Ä¢ Positive attitude and strong work ethic

This is a great opportunity to gain experience on an independent feature film and work with a passionate, creative team!

‚ö†Ô∏è ONLY SEEKING PEOPLE FOR THESE POSITIONS. PLEASE DO NOT SUBMIT FOR ANY OTHERS.

üìß TO APPLY: Please DO NOT send direct messages. Please only submit your resume with a message detailing your interest to info@saltpicturesco.com with the subject line "SWING GRIP" or "PA #1" or "PA #2"

Cinematographer and Project details:
(Photo attached of cast call) 

Hello everyone! 

Myself and another are co-producing a sci-fi short film and are looking for a cinematographer. 

The film follows the events leading up to beginning of an apocalyptic world. Where the people required to re-start society are trapped in a safe house. 

This is a small indie project, which is being self-funded, so this is an unpaid role, as the budget will be going towards locations, costuming, food, etc. However there is a possible opportunity to be given a room to stay overnight on set. 

The dates will be the 28th, 29th, 30th of November. 
The location is a little TBD but will be in the vicinity of Brisbane/GC (likely towards Brisbane). 

The genre: Sci-fi 
Estimated # of actors: 8 

There will be a variety of different skin tones, so needs to know how to light them accordingly without washing anyone out or darkening them. 

For any questions or if interested in the position please email  a.to.z.infinite.8@gmail.com

items.text:
Probably a weird question, I wrote a screenplay for a pilot and I was wondering if anyone had any advice about the next steps on getting it in the hands of someone that could produce it. I just need a chance to submit it and see where it goes. Does anyone have any experience with this. 

Long time writer, first time writing a pilot.

topComments.text:
Every pilot that I‚Äôve worked on has had financial investments in order to produce at least the teaser. If not the full episode.

Even when Elijah would wanted the role of Frodo and Lord of the rings, he just put together a teaser trailer with himself in it to sell the idea that‚Äôs essentially what a pilot is 

Trying to sell the idea of a story, not necessarily the production company that puts it together Ôøº
Start posting for the people you need .. editing.. actors,directors.youll get people that want to be a part of it and help

Bitte l√∂schen, falls es nicht passt - aber es hat ja trotzdem etwas mit "Darsteller" sein zu tun und wir konnten erst letztens 3 Personen √ºber diese Gruppe vermitteln.

+++ Darsteller als Weihnachtmann in Einkaufszentrum  +++

+++ Darstellerin als Wichtel/Engel in Einkaufszentrum  +++

WAS SUCHEN WIR:

In einem Shopping-Center im Saarland suchen wir f√ºr knapp 4 Wochen einen Darsteller als Weihnachtsmann und eine Darstellerin am Weihnachtswichtel oder Engel. Dabei betreut man eine Weihnachtsgondel und empf√§ngt Kinder, dann nat√ºrlich auch mit dem Weihnachtsmann sprechen d√ºrfen.

Kost√ºme werden gestellt

WANN: 27.11. - 24.12. (ohne die Sonntage) Unterschiedlicher Tagesaufwand zwischen 4 und 6 Stunden)

WO:  Neunkirchen (Saarland)

WAS: Betreuung einer Weihnachtsgondel als Weihnachtsmann / Wichtel

HONORAR:

- Es kommt so ein bisschen drauf an zu wieviele Termine ihr √ºbernehmen k√∂nnt. Grunds√§tzlich k√∂nnen wir je nach Auslastung 20-25 Euro anbieten. Sollte man wirklich an allen Tagen k√∂nnen w√§re das zw. 2500 und 3000 Euro.

- Zus√§tzlich kann man dar√ºber nachdenken, ob wir euch ein Deutschlandticket f√ºr den Monat bezahlen oder evtl. ein AirBnB bezahlen.

Voraussetzungen Weihnachtsmann:

-          Alter ca. 30-60 Jahre

-          Extrovertiert, Freundlich

-          Typ "Weihnachtsmann"

Voraussetzungen Wichtel/Engel:

-          Alter ca. 20-35 Jahre

-          Extrovertiert, Freundlich

Abrechnung:

-          Am liebsten √ºber euer Kleingewerbe

-          oder wir melden euch f√ºr den Zeitraum an

Bewerbungen & Fragen bitte an jobs@fishershouse.de

Bitte schickt uns direkt 2-3 passende Fotos von euch mit, damit wir uns einen Eindruck von euch machen k√∂nnen.

Schickt uns bitte au√üerdem die Information, an welchen Tagen ihr Zeitraum ihr verf√ºgbar seid. Ihr m√ºsst nicht an jedem Tag k√∂nnen, aber nat√ºrlich w√§re m√∂glichst h√§ufig super :-)

**UL√òNNET**

Vi er et hold fra Potemkin, Den Jyske Filmskole, der er i gang med vores afgangsprojekt

Vi s√∏ger en mand i spillealderen 18-23 til hovedrollen Milo

Kort om historien:
En ung mand med et spiralerende heroinmisbrug vender hjem til sin syge mor for f√∏rste gang i m√•nedsvis. Han kommer for at bede om penge - men ender som et stille opg√∏r mellem k√¶rlighed og skam. Vi √∏nsker ikke at lave en film som glorificerer stoffer, men om, hvordan det nedbryder de st√¶rkeste relationer mellem mennesker.

Om rollen:
Milo er 23 og fanget i sit eget forfald. Bag afh√¶ngigheden gemmer sig en s√∏n, der stadig elsker sin mor, men ikke l√¶ngere kan b√¶re at blive set af hende. Skylden, k√¶rligheden og skammen eksisterer side om side i ham.
Rollen kr√¶ver en skuespiller med evnen til at udtrykke mere gennem stilhed end gennem ord - en fysisk og f√∏lelsesm√¶ssig tilstedev√¶relse, hvor sm√• reaktioner og blikke fort√¶ller alt.

Praktisk:
Optagelserne finder sted i Aarhus den 24. og 25. november.
Der vil v√¶re fuld forplejning p√• settet, men vi vil ikke kunne betale k√∏n, transport eller overnatning.

Hvis du er interesseret i at blive taget i betragtning til rollen, bedes du indsende et kort selftape af dummy teksten, der er vedh√¶ftet i opslaget. Send det meget gerne til mailen nedenfor.

Vi h√•ber, at projektet v√¶kker din nysgerrighed - og at du har lyst til at tage del i fort√¶llingen om Milo og hans mor.

Med venlig hilsen
